html.body: Subunits CD300LB, CD300LF, CD300LG, CD300LD, CD300E

We summarize here how NPD1 elicits neuroprotection by up-regulating c-REL, a nuclear factor (NF)-B subtype that, in turn, enhances expression of BIRC3 (baculoviral inhibitor of apoptosis repeat-containing protein 3) in the retina and in experimental stroke, leading to neuroprotection.
